Hi,&nbsp;  
  Please see below for an email received from you guys. Can you please help direct me on how to do this so I don't run into disruptions for my business moving forward?&nbsp;  
   Hi there,We're reaching out with an important update that directly affects your&nbsp;FedEx Shipping Plugin for WooCommerce with Print Label.&nbsp;FedEx has officially announced the retirement of its legacy Web Services (SOAP) APIs, and all merchants using FedEx for shipping must migrate to FedEx REST APIs to avoid disruption.As a FedEx Certified Compatible Solution Provider, the FedEx Shipping Plugin for WooCommerce with Print Label is fully prepared for REST APIs.&nbsp;We've already completed verification and production readiness — so the transition on your end is straightforward.What's HappeningFedEx is permanently retiring its Web Services platform. If you're currently using legacy Web Services credentials (meter number, authentication key, etc.) in your FedEx Shipping Plugin for WooCommerce with Print Label, those credentials will stop working according to the following timeline:Migration Timeline•March 31, 2026&nbsp;— Final provider API verification &amp; production readiness deadline•April 1, 2026&nbsp;— Meter deactivation window begins; Web Services retirement starts•June 1, 2026&nbsp;— Final Web Services shutdown (all legacy endpoints permanently offline)What This Means for YouIf no action is taken,&nbsp;your FedEx shipping rates, label printing, and tracking functionality within the plugin may be affected after April 1, 2026.&nbsp;This could impact your ability to display shipping rates, print FedEx labels, and fulfill orders from your WooCommerce store.How to Migrate (3 Simple Steps)1Register for FedEx REST APIs Complete the registration directly from within the plugin settings. You'll need to provide your account and contact details — name, company name, phone number, email, and the complete business address associated with your FedEx account.&nbsp;Validate Your FedEx Account Choose a verification method to confirm your identity:• OTP via SMS• OTP via Phone Call• OTP via Email• Invoice• Help Desk2Credentials Configured Automatically Once registration and validation are complete, your new REST API credentials will be configured automatically within the plugin. No manual key entry required.3Test &amp; Confirm Run a test shipment or rate request to verify that shipping rates display correctly and label printing works as expected with the new REST API credentials. 

   Thank you, Duong Pham | Manager&nbsp; Sunshine Nail &amp; Beauty Supply, LLC
 4833 South 72nd Street&nbsp;  Omaha, NE 68127&nbsp;  Tel: (402) 884-5972

